body:
@zakkak I can confirm I can reproduce the issue with the provided reproducer.

I have no idea what's going on. `org.eclipse.angus.activation.nativeimage.AngusActivationFeature` is a simple GraalVM feature that is referenced in a `native-image.properties`, I fail to see how it could create this issue. To be honest, I haven't seen this issue much, the message seems to imply the class only popped up at runtime and wasn't around at static init.

I checked the dependency tree in both deployment and runtime modes and things look fine.
